# Example CLAUDE.md (Global)

## Destructive Operations
Irreversible operations (TRUNCATE, DROP, bulk DELETE, schema changes) require approval before execution.
Format: "I'm about to do X. Impact: Y. Alternative: W. Proceed?"

## Multi-Agent Routing
Pick the first matching condition:

| Condition | Method |
|-----------|--------|
| Single research/exploration/file read | **Subagent** (Explore, background) |
| 2-5 independent file edits | **Subagent + worktree isolation** |
| Cross-cutting work (front+back+test) | **Agent Teams** (TeamCreate) |
| Competing hypotheses, multi-angle review | **Agent Teams** (3-5 agents) |
| Complex single task, autonomous | **/ultrawork** |
| Manual multi-session (user intervention) | **cmux** |

**Rules:**
- Specify clear completion criteria when delegating
- No parallel edits on shared files — sequential only
- Agent Teams: file ownership separation (no concurrent edits on same file)

## Context Management
- `/clear` on task switch
- Delegate bulk file reads to subagents (protect main context)
- `/compact` when performance degrades in long sessions

## Code Quality
- Workflow: explore → plan → code → test
- Read 2-3 existing files before writing new code — follow patterns
- One session = one feature

## Git Convention
Conventional Commits (feat:, fix:, refactor:, docs:, chore:). Review changes before commit.
